THIS FILE IS NOTE ON HOW TO CONFIGURE PERSISTENT MOUNTING OF NFS

TO DO IT GO TO
$ sudo nano /etc/fstab

AND ADD THIS CONTENT AT THE EOF

192.168.0.68:/media/myshare	/mnt/myshare	nfs	defaults	0	0 

- WE CAN USE softmount INSTEAD OF defaults WHICH WILL DONT TRY TO REACH THE NFS SERVER IF IT IS NOT AVAILABLE
- ALSO THER IS hardmount WHICH WILL KEEP ON TRY CONTACTING THE SERVER EVEN IF IT IS UNAVAILABLE
- NOW DO 
$ mount -a or $ reboot

AND THEN  
$ df -h
